bank on it, and be prepared for a hot, crowded journey. it should cost no more than a few thousand rupiah per person (ask the driver beforehand). there's also an air conditioned bus service called trans sarbagita that runs following route term. batu bulan (gianyar) - tohpati (dps) - sanur (dps) - kuta central park (badung) - jimbaran (badung) - nusa dua (badung), occassionally the bus heading to and from nusa dua will stop at the airport. there is no marked trans sarbagita bus stop at the airport. bus stops at the roundabout at the left side from the airport 